&gt;&gt; A lot.

00:00:27.130 --> 00:00:29.680
&gt;&gt; Identical twins are actually a really

00:00:29.680 --> 00:00:31.970
useful tool for scientists to determine heritablity.

00:00:31.970 --> 00:00:34.180
&gt;&gt; But aren't there different types of twins?

00:00:34.180 --> 00:00:37.550
&gt;&gt; Well there are. there are identical and there're fraternal

00:00:37.550 --> 00:00:40.470
twins. We also refer to them as Monozygotic and Dizygotic.

00:00:41.570 --> 00:00:42.730
&gt;&gt; Wait mono what?

00:00:42.730 --> 00:00:45.253
&gt;&gt; Monozygotic and dizygotic.

00:00:45.253 --> 00:00:45.775
&gt;&gt; Oh.

00:00:45.775 --> 00:00:50.480
&gt;&gt; Monozygotic means that they came from same fertilized egg or zygote.

00:00:50.480 --> 00:00:55.810
Dizygotic means in a came from two different fertilized eggs or two different

00:00:55.810 --> 00:01:00.092
zygotes. So genetically identical twins, do you

